# Definition of Done

Source: `assets/docs/guides/DoD.md`. Automated checks: `bun run typecheck`, `bun run lint`, `bun test` (and pre-commit where configured).

## 1. Requirements → Tests

When implementing a requirement from a spec under `assets/docs/specs/` (e.g. `assets/docs/specs/kli/`):

- At least one test per acceptance criterion where it applies
- Follow `assets/docs/guides/TESTING_GUIDE.md` and `.cursor/rules/testing.mdc` (Bun test, minimal mocking, table-driven where helpful)

## 2. Best Practices

- Follow `assets/docs/guides/CODESTYLE_GUIDE.md` and `.cursor/rules/codestyle.mdc`
- Code: shortest, clearest, self-explanatory, non-redundant
- Architecture: see `assets/docs/guides/FCIS.guide.md` when using core/shell split

## 3. Learn and Document

- When you establish a new team-wide practice, add it to the relevant guide under `assets/docs/guides/`

## 4–6. Automated Checks

- No TypeScript errors — `bun run typecheck`
- No linter failures — `bun run lint`
- All tests pass — `bun test`

## 7. Task tracking

- When a spec includes `tasks.md`, mark completed items there

## 8. Git commit

- Follow `assets/docs/guides/GIT_COMMITS_GUIDE.md` (and `.cursor/rules/git-commits.mdc`)
- Pre-commit / gitlint must pass where enabled
